The paper deals with optimization problems related to graph homomorphisms, which are typically studied in the areas of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The specific problem of finding minimum cost homomorphisms is related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and combinatorial optimization (cs.CC). The paper also involves the study of dichotomy classifications, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.GT).
